Name: DateTime
Description: The date/time that the game is scheduled to be played in UTC

Name: Status
Description: Indicates the game's status. Possible values include: Scheduled; InProgress; Break; Final; Awarded; Postponed; Canceled; Suspended. If a game is called off before it starts; the Status is set to Postponed; until a new date/time is scheduled; at which point; the DateTime is updated; and the Status is set back to Scheduled. If a game has already started; and temporarily interrupted; it's Status is set to Suspended; until it either resumes; or gets postponed and replayed at a later date. If the game is on break; then the Status will be Break. Awarded is used in cases where a game is decided without completing. That means that a game was decided by the Federation/League to one team for a reason. This can include situations like riots; where the opponent team gets 3:0 win awarded as punishment. Awarded is also used when a club withdraws during the season from the competition then all the remaining matches getting awarded 3:0.

Name: SlateID
Description: Unique ID of a Slate (assigned by FantasyData).

Name: Operator
Description: The name of the operator who is running contests for this slate. Possible values: FanDuel; DraftKings; Yahoo; FantasyDraft; etc.

Name: OperatorSlateID
Description: Unique ID of a slate (assigned by the operator).

Name: OperatorName
Description: The name of the slate (assigned by the operator). Possible values: Main; Express; Arcade; Late Night; etc.

Name: OperatorDay
Description: The day (in UTC) that the slate begins (assigned by the operator).

Name: OperatorStartTime
Description: The date/time (in UTC) that the slate begins (assigned by the operator).

Name: NumberOfGames
Description: The number of actual games that this slate covers.

Name: IsMultiDaySlate
Description: Whether this slate uses games that take place on different days.

Name: RemovedByOperator
Description: Indicates whether this slate was removed/deleted by the operator.

Name: OperatorGameType
Description: The game type of the slate. Will often be null as most operators only have one game type.

Name: DfsSlateGames
Description: The games that are included in this slate

Name: DfsSlatePlayers
Description: The players that are included in this slate

Name: SlateRosterSlots
Description: The positions that need to be filled for this particular slate

Name: SalaryCap
Description: The salary cap for the current slate (is null for slates with no salary cap such a Tiers gametypes)

Name: VideoGameId
Description: The Id of the video game related to this slate (CS:GO; LOL; etc.)

Name: SlateGameID
Description: Unique ID of a SlateGame (assigned by FantasyData).

Name: SlateID
Description: The SlateID that this SlateGame refers to.

Name: GameID
Description: The FantasyData GameID that this SlateGame refers to. This points to data in the respective sports' schedule/game/box score feeds.

Name: Game
Description: The details of the Game that this SlateGame refers to.

Name: OperatorGameID
Description: Unique ID of a SlateGame (assigned by the operator).

Name: RemovedByOperator
Description: Indicates whether this game was removed/deleted by the operator.

Name: SlatePlayerID
Description: Unique ID of a SlatePlayer (assigned by FantasyData).

Name: SlateID
Description: The SlateID that this SlatePlayer refers to.

Name: SlateGameID
Description: The SlateGameID that this SlatePlayer refers to.

Name: PlayerID
Description: The FantasyData PlayerID that this SlatePlayer refers to. This points to data in the respective sports' player feeds.

Name: PlayerGameProjectionStatID
Description: The FantasyData StatID that this SlatePlayer refers to. This points to data in the respective sports' projected player game stats feeds.

Name: OperatorPlayerID
Description: Unique ID of the Player (assigned by the operator).

Name: OperatorSlatePlayerID
Description: Unique ID of the SlatePlayer (assigned by the operator).

Name: OperatorPlayerName
Description: The player's name (assigned by the operator).

Name: OperatorPosition
Description: The player's eligible positions for the contest (assigned by the operator).

Name: OperatorSalary
Description: The player's salary for the contest (assigned by the operator).

Name: OperatorRosterSlots
Description: The player's eligible positions to be played in the contest (assigned by the operator). This would include UTIL; etc plays for those that are eligible.

Name: RemovedByOperator
Description: Indicates whether this player was removed/deleted by the operator.

Name: Team
Description: Name of the team to which the player is associated.

Name: TeamID
Description: Unique ID of the Team to which the player is associated.
